public Books.Mylibrary.Bookshelves.MoveVolume moveVolume(String shelf,
                                                         String volumeId,
                                                         Integer volumePosition)
                                                  throws IOException
Moves a volume within a bookshelf. Create a request for the method "bookshelves.moveVolume". This request holds the parameters needed by the the books server. After setting any optional parameters, call the Books.Mylibrary.Bookshelves.MoveVolume.execute() method to invoke the remote operation.

Parameters:
shelf - ID of bookshelf with the volume.
volumeId - ID of volume to move.
volumePosition - Position on shelf to move the item (0 puts the item before the current first item, 1 puts it between the first and the second and so on.)
Returns:
the request

public Books.Mylibrary.Bookshelves.Volumes volumes()
